-- Brasil Telecom Former Board Members Settle with CVM
-- B y   H e l d e r   M a r i n h o
-- 2012-05-24T19:31:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-24/brasil-telecom-former-board-members-settle-with-cvm-correct-.html
(Corrects name of second former Brasil Telecom board member
in second paragraph.)  Two former board members of Brasil
Telecom Participacoes SA reached a settlement with  Brazil ’s
securities regulator CVM, ending an accusation of not complying
with local legislation.  Veronica Valente Dantas agreed to pay 300,000 reais to CVM,
while Eduardo Penido Monteiro will pay 200,000 reais, CVM said
today in an e-mailed statement.  In a separate case, Ricardo Antunes Carneiro Neto, former
investor relations director at  LLX Logistica SA (LLXL3) , also reached a
settlement with CVM, agreeing to pay 200,000 reais, the
regulator said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helder Marinho in Sao Paulo at 
 hmarinho@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Taís Fuoco at 
 tfuoco1@bloomberg.net  